A dying tree can be chopped down to provide logs and 25 Woodcutting experience. They are the same as normal trees but with a different look, and can be found around Varrock and the Lumber Yard.

Contents

  • 1 Woodcutting info
  • 2 Mechanics
    • 2.1 Cut chance
  • 3 Additional drops
  • 4 Trivia
  • 5 References

Woodcutting info[edit | edit source]

Dying tree
Level required 1
Woodcutting XP25 xp
Required toolAxe
Respawn time35.4 - 58.8 seconds
Item Quantity Rarity Price High Alch
Logs1Common502

Mechanics[edit | edit source]

Dying trees have the exact same mechanics as regular trees, giving logs and always depleting after one section cut. The tree respawns between 36–60 seconds, randomly, and is not influenced by world population.[1] The chance to successfully chop is affected by the axe used and Woodcutting level, better axes and a higher woodcutting level increases the likelihood of successfully receiving a log. Kandarin headgear 1 and above gives double logs when cutting them.

Additional drops[edit | edit source]

  • Beaver – Dying trees have a chance to drop the beaver Woodcutting pet. At level 1 Woodcutting there is a 1 in 317,622 chance to receive the beaver and a 1 in 315,172 chance at level 99.
  • Clue nest – Dying trees can drop all clue nests. At level 1 Woodcutting there is an approximately 1 in 3145 chance to receive an easy-elite clue nest and a 1 in 1596 chance at level 99. Beginner clue nests have a universal 1 in 1000 chance to be dropped.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • While dying trees drop clue nests, they do not drop any other type of bird nest.[2]

A '''dying tree''' can be chopped down to provide [[logs]] and 25 [[Woodcutting]] experience. They are the same as normal [[tree]]s but with a different look, and can be found around [[Varrock]] and the [[Lumber Yard]].

==Woodcutting info==
{{Woodcutting info
|name = Dying tree
|level = 1
|xp = 25
|tool = [[Axe]]
|time = 35.4 - 58.8 seconds
}}

{{DropsTableHead}}
{{DropsLineSkill|name=Logs|quantity=1|rarity=Common|skill=Woodcutting}}
{{DropsTableBottom}}

==Mechanics==
Dying trees have the exact same mechanics as regular trees, giving logs and always depleting after one section cut.
The tree respawns between 36–60 seconds, randomly, and is not influenced by world population.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1161764474078015490|date=14 August 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/TCO64|archivedate=30 May 2020}}
The chance to successfully chop is affected by the [[axe]] used and Woodcutting level, better axes and a higher woodcutting level increases the likelihood of successfully receiving a log.
[[Kandarin headgear 1]] and above gives double logs when cutting them.

===Cut chance===

|label6=Adamant|low6=192|high6=600|req6=31|color6=seagreen|image6=Adamant axe.png
|label7=Rune|low7=224|high7=700|req7=41|color7=steelblue|image7=Rune axe.png
|label8=Dragon|low8=240|high8=750|req8=61|color8=firebrick|image8=Dragon axe.png
}}

==Additional drops==
*[[Beaver]] – Dying trees have a chance to drop the beaver Woodcutting pet. At level 1 Woodcutting there is a '''1 in 317,622''' chance to receive the beaver and a '''1 in 315,172''' chance at level 99.
*[[Clue nest]] – Dying trees can drop all clue nests. At level 1 Woodcutting there is an approximately '''1 in 3145''' chance to receive an easy-elite clue nest and a '''1 in 1596''' chance at level 99. Beginner clue nests have a universal '''1 in 1000''' chance to be dropped. 

==Trivia==
*While dying trees drop clue nests, they do not drop any other type of [[bird nest]].{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1514299817513697289|date=13 April 2022|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/5DKJY|archivedate=17 April 2022|quote=Basic trees, whether evergreen-shaped or not, never offer those as far as I can see in their code. Hence my surprise when you said Settled got a seed that way. I think you're clear to update your ruleset.|notes=|name=|group=}}
